%% PipelineKit — Pipeline Execution Flow (Engineering / Debugging)
%% Audience: engineers debugging pipelinekit run.
%% Sequence verified against src/pipelinekit/runtime/runner.py (run()).
%% The run record is updated in a try/finally — it is NEVER skipped, even on failure.
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant CLI as CLI (run.py)
    participant Loader as config.loader
    participant Runner as PipelineRunner
    participant State as state.db
    participant Adapters as Adapters (dlt / dbt / Soda)
    participant Notifier as NotificationDispatcher

    User->>CLI: pipelinekit run
    CLI->>Loader: load_config()
    alt config invalid
        Loader-->>CLI: ConfigurationError (PK-CONFIG-001..004)
        CLI-->>User: print error, exit 1
    end
    Loader-->>CLI: PipelineConfig
    CLI->>Runner: run()
    Runner->>State: insert_run(run_id, status=pending)

    Note over Runner,Adapters: Enabled steps only, in order: ingestion, transformation, quality

    loop each enabled adapter
        Runner->>Adapters: execute_step(name, adapter)
        alt step succeeds
            Adapters-->>Runner: StepResult(SUCCESS, rows, duration)
        else step fails
            Adapters-->>Runner: StepResult(FAILED, error_code e.g. PK-ADAPTER-001/002)
        end
    end

    Note over Runner: aggregate status (SUCCESS / PARTIAL / FAILED).<br/>Unexpected exception, error_code = PK-RUNTIME-001

    Runner->>State: update_run(final status, duration, error_code) [try/finally]

    opt notifications.enabled
        Runner->>Notifier: notify_pipeline_result(result)
        Note over Notifier: failure swallowed — never corrupts state (SPEC-008)
    end

    Runner-->>CLI: PipelineResult (per-step status, duration, rows)
    CLI-->>User: render run table, exit 0 if succeeded else 1

    Note over CLI,State: Data contract DEFINITIONS are checked by<br/>pipelinekit validate --contracts (PK-CONTRACT-*);<br/>data-quality checks run in the Soda step above.
